neuroscience,
especially the cognitive

00:28:42.821 --> 00:28:44.420
neuroscience of faces.

00:28:47.710 --> 00:28:49.871
Dr.
Susan Nolen-Hoeksema is the

00:28:49.871 --> 00:28:53.690
world's authority on depression,
and in particular,

00:28:53.690 --> 00:28:56.445
on sex differences and
depression, and she's going to

00:28:56.445 --> 00:28:58.990
talk about this towards the end
of the course.

00:28:58.990 --> 00:29:05.122
Kelly Brownell is going to
talk--is head of the Rudd

00:29:05.122 --> 00:29:09.649
Center, focuses on obesity,
eating disorders,

00:29:09.649 --> 00:29:12.950
dieting, and he'll talk about
the psychology of food.

00:29:12.950 --> 00:29:14.632
And finally,
Dr.

00:29:14.632 --> 00:29:18.558
Peter Salovey,
Dean of Yale College,

00:29:18.558 --> 00:29:24.392
is going to come to us on
Valentine's Day and tell us

00:29:24.392 --> 00:29:30.450
everything he knows about the
mysteries of love.

00:29:30.450 --> 00:29:33.812
All of these details are in the
syllabus and I'll stick around

00:29:33.812 --> 00:29:37.000
and answer questions.
Hope to see you next week.

